               <state type="martyr" source="#bibl1253-1">
                  <p>Martyr</p>
               </state>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl1253-1">Bedjan, appendice a Jab-Alaha, 347-94. BHO, 353. Hoffmann, Ausziige, 78- 86. Devos, "Martyrs persans", 216.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Gregory Pīrānguŝnasp was a Zoroastrian Convert from the family of Mihran. He was imprisoned by the Byzantines and treated well by Justin I. He converted to Christianity. He was freed by a truce with Kusro, but his family put him to death in 542.</note>
